    <h1 class="entry-title custom-heading page-heading"><span class="hide-title"><span>About Myself</span></span></h1>
    <p>Hello! My name is Asaf Bilker, and I'm a software developer based in Israel. I'm passionate about creating
        beautiful and responsive websites that provide optimal user experiences. I have experience with a range of
        technologies including Python, Flask, HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.</p>

    <p>In addition to my work as a web developer, I'm also a professional handball player, currently playing for H.C
        Rehovot. I love the sport and have been playing it since 2016. I've also served in the intelligence section of
        the military as an outstanding sportsman from 2016 to 2019.</p>

    <p>I'm currently studying computer science at Tel Aviv University, Before I began my studies at Tel Aviv University,
        I studied at the Open University of Israel as a student in a program called "Transfer Pathway" or "Afik Maavar".
        I completed the program successfully, achieving a GPA of 89. I also have a background in biology, having
        completed 5 units of biology and 5 units of English in high school.</p>

    <p>I'm skilled in a variety of programming languages including Python, JavaScript, Java, C, and SQL. I'm also
        experienced with Git, Linux, algorithm design and analysis, and data structures.</p>

    <p>I'm always looking for new opportunities and challenges, and I'd love to hear from you if you think we could work
        together. You can reach me by sending an email or connecting with me on LinkedIn,
        here - <a href="/contact" class="contact-button">Contact</a> . I look
        forward to hearing from you!</p>
</div>

